<br>
Skald primary stats are CHA, STR and CON. All of those are of the highest priority for every skald.<br>
<br>
Strength as an effect on your weapon damage (all &quot;viking&quot; weapons are strength based) and your carrying capacity. It is your most important &quot;combat&quot; statistics.<br>
<br>
Constitution improves your base hit points.<br>
<br>
Dexterity has an effect on how well you parry, block, and evade (in a smaller way). It does NOT have any effect on any offensive ability. While a lot of skalds appreciate high dexterity, and it is definitely helpful, keep however in mind that, by design, the skald has extremely low defensive abilities so a high dexterity will have less of an impact than a high dexterity score for an assassin or a shield tank.<br>
<br>
Quickness help a little with evade and increase your attack speed. Quickness has two drawbacks. The first one is the &quot;haste cap&quot;, that can be reached with a high quickness, a fast weapon and a buff (however, many skalds favor slower weapons, so this is not a real problem). The second one is that, while your damage per second definitely increase, quickness slightly reduces the amount of damage inflicted by your styled hits, so can be detrimental in very short fights, where massivie intial damage counts. Despite those drawbacks, more quickness is (generally) good, however, it is a matter of prority, and many skald will only strive to improve their quickness after having maxed other significant stats.<br>
<br>
Charisma is the skald &quot;casting skill&quot;. It increases the damage of the skald's damage shouts (not a lot, but it is still noticeable). It improves the skald's power pool. It is unclear wether or not it helps the resistance rates on spells. Charisma can NOT be boosted by &quot;acuity&quot; buffs.<br>
<br>
All other statistics (intelligence, piety and empathy) are wothless and meaningless for a skald.<br>
